MINIMALISM CHECK (P5 — 5W1H gate for this skill's existence):
- Who: Running replicant host (P12 — `replicant_host` mandatory).
- What: Runtime signal / classified threat pattern.
- Where: Local CNS telemetry stream (NOT workspace manifest — distinct from supply-chain-sentinel).
- When: Continuous — observes spans as emitted (not audit cycle).
- Why: P3.1 (Generative Space requires safe container — runtime blocking is floor, not ceiling; static audit cannot detect runtime anomalies); P1 (User Sovereignty — user controls which runtime signals are monitored); P4 (Clear Boundaries — runtime telemetry boundary, distinct from manifest boundary); P9 (Homeostatic Regulation — runtime threat must be observable via `cns.runtime.*` spans).
- How: Observe signal → classify → map taxonomy → emit CNS span → (next phase: emit regulation + propose regression).
- If any of these 6 were missing, this skill would violate P5. All 6 are present.

